  "text": "In our study, we used Mean Shift Clustering Procedure (MSCP), a nonparametric clustering process closely related to density estimation, as an initial processing step to segment images by clustering features associated with image pixels/super-pixels in a feature space. Generally speaking, the overall goal of MSCP is to detect unknown number of modes (local maxima) of an unknown empirical probability density function in a feature space [CITATION_1] . The identified modes of the feature density distribution can then be used to structure clusters of data nearby.",
